Temperatures in Johannesburg alone are expected to reach&#160;33 degrees Celsius. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service is warning a heatwave will hit the Gauteng province over the next four days.Temperatures in Johannesburg alone are expected to reach 33 degrees Celsius. Rainfall is also expected over most of the province, with a chance of isolated thundershowers this evening. The weathers service s Kholofelo Mahlangu said, We're expecting temperatures up to 35 degree Celsius in Pretoria, 33 for Johannesburg and 33 for Vereeniging. These temperatures are going to be more or less this much for the next four days, that is why we have an alert for a heatwave. 